data: {"index":0,"blockType":"text","finalContent":"<thinking>\nLet me analyze the results from the first 4 parallel calls:\n\n1. **flowise_list_chatflows** - 401 Unauthorized (no auth token). This is an auth issue, not a Flowise issue.\n2. **flowise_list_nodes** - 401 Unauthorized (same issue).\n3. **flowise_health_check** - ✅ Healthy! Status: healthy, URL: http://openagentic-api:8000/api/flowise-workspace, timestamp: 2026-02-20T22:01:51.652424\n4. **flowise_get_creation_guide** - ✅ Success! Got full guide with templates, patterns, rules.\n\nThe 401 errors on list_chatflows and list_nodes indicate the Flowise API requires authentication tokens that aren't being passed. The health_check and creation_guide work because they don't hit the authenticated Flowise API endpoints (or use a different auth path).\n\nLet me proceed with Step 5 - create the chatflow using a template. The guide recommends using templateId for guaranteed working flows. I'll use the \"llm_chain\" template since the user asked for a \"basic LLM chain configuration\".\n</thinking>\n\nSteps 1–4 returned. Two auth issues noted, two successes. Proceeding to **Step 5** — create the chatflow using the recommended template approach from the creation guide."}

