event: content_block_stop
data: {"index":0,"blockType":"text","finalContent":"<thinking>\nNow I have a clear picture. The pattern is:\n\n**Succeeds (local MCP server operations, no Flowise API call):**\n- `flowise_health_check` — ✅ (but misleading - it reports \"healthy\" while get_framework_status reports \"unhealthy\")\n- `flowise_get_creation_guide` — ✅ (static guide, no API call)\n- `flowise_list_templates` — ✅ (static template list, no API call)\n- `get_framework_status` — ✅ (but shows Flowise as unhealthy)\n\n**Fails (actual Flowise API calls):**\n- `flowise_list_chatflows` — ❌ 401 Unauthorized\n- `flowise_list_nodes` — ❌ 401 Unauthorized\n- `flowise_create_chatflow` — ❌ 401 Unauthorized\n- `flowise_create_from_template` — ❌ 401 Unauthorized\n- `flowise_create_chatflow_advanced` — ❌ 401 Unauthorized\n\nThe root cause is clear: The Flowise workspace API endpoint (`http://openagentic-api:8000/api/flowise-workspace`) is either:\n1. Not properly authenticating OBO tokens from the MCP proxy\n2. Not receiving the authentication token at all\n\nThis is consistent with the previous audit findings where Flowise was marked as ❌ Unhealthy across all 3 audits.\n\nLet me compile the full lifecycle test report.\n</thinking>\n\nAll data collected. Here is the complete lifecycle test report.\n\n---\n\n## Lifecycle Test Results Summary\n\n**Test Executed:** 2026-02-20T22:01:51Z\n**Target Endpoint:** `http://openagentic-api:8000/api/flowise-workspace`\n\n| Step | Operation | Tool | Status | Detail |\n|:----:|-----------|------|:------:|--------|\n| 1 | **List chatflows** | `flowise_list_chatflows` | ❌ | `401 Unauthorized — No authentication token provided` |\n| 2 | **List nodes** | `flowise_list_nodes` | ❌ | `401 Unauthorized — No authentication token provided` |\n| 3 | **Health check** | `flowise_health_check` | ✅ | Healthy — `2026-02-20T22:01:51.652424` |\n| 4 | **Creation guide** | `flowise_get_creation_guide` | ✅ | 5 templates, chatOpenAgentic patterns, critical rules returned |\n| 5 | **Create chatflow** | `flowise_create_chatflow` | ❌ | `401 Unauthorized — No authentication token provided` |\n| 5b | **Create (alt)** | `flowise_create_from_template` | ❌ | `401 Unauthorized — identical failure` |\n| 5c | **Create (advanced)** | `flowise_create_chatflow_advanced` | ❌ | `401 Unauthorized — identical failure` |\n| 6 | **Validate flow** | — | ⏭️ Skipped | Dependency on Step 5 (no chatflow created) |\n| 7 | **Verify creation** | — | ⏭️ Skipped | Dependency on Step 5 |\n| 8 | **Analytics** | — | ⏭️ Skipped | Dependency on Step 5 |\n| 9 | **Delete chatflow** | — | ⏭️ Skipped | Dependency on Step 5 |\n| 10 | **Verify deletion** | — | ⏭️ Skipped | Dependency on Step 5 |\n\n**Overall: 2 passed / 5 failed / 5 skipped (cascading dependency)**\n\n---\n\n## Root Cause Analysis\n\n### Two-Tier Architecture Split\n\nThe Flowise MCP server operates with a **split behavior** — some functions are served locally while others proxy to the Flowise backend API:\n\n```diagram\n{\n  \"type\": \"flowchart\",\n  \"title\": \"Flowise MCP Authentication Failure Chain\",\n  \"layout\": \"horizontal\",\n  \"nodes\": [\n    {\"id\": \"user\", \"label\": \"Lifecycle Test\\n(10 steps)\", \"shape\": \"rounded\", \"color\": \"primary\"},\n    {\"id\": \"mcp\", \"label\": \"Flowise MCP\\nServer\", \"shape\": \"hexagon\", \"color\": \"warning\"},\n    {\"id\": \"local\", \"label\": \"Local Functions\\n(guide, templates,\\nhealth check)\", \"shape\": \"rounded\", \"color\": \"success\"},\n    {\"id\": \"api\", \"label\": \"Flowise API\\nopenagentic-api:8000\\n/api/flowise-workspace\", \"shape\": \"cylinder\", \"color\": \"error\"},\n    {\"id\": \"result_ok\", \"label\": \"✅ Success\\n(Steps 3, 4)\", \"shape\": \"circle\", \"color\": \"success\"},\n    {\"id\": \"result_fail\", \"label\": \"❌ 401\\nUnauthorized\\n(Steps 1, 2, 5)\", \"shape\": \"circle\", \"color\": \"error\"}\n  ],\n  \"edges\": [\n    {\"source\": \"user\", \"target\": \"mcp\", \"label\": \"All 10 steps\"},\n    {\"source\": \"mcp\", \"target\": \"local\", \"label\": \"Static data\", \"style\": \"solid\"},\n    {\"source\": \"mcp\", \"target\": \"api\", \"label\": \"OBO Token ❌\", \"style\": \"dashed\"},\n    {\"source\": \"local\", \"target\": \"result_ok\"},\n    {\"source\": \"api\", \"target\": \"result_fail\", \"label\": \"No auth token\", \"style\": \"dashed\"}\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n### What Worked (Local MCP Functions)\n\n| Function | Response | Notes |\n|----------|----------|-------|\n| **`flowise_health_check`** | `status: healthy` | Reports healthy — but contradicted by `get_framework_status` |\n| **`flowise_get_creation_guide`** | Full guide returned | 5 templates, chatOpenAgentic model, edge rules |\n| **`flowise_list_templates`** | 5 templates listed | `simple_conversation`, `conversation_with_memory`, `tool_agent`, `rag_conversation`, `llm_chain` |\n\n### What Failed (Flowise API Proxied Calls)\n\nEvery call that requires the MCP proxy to forward an **OBO (On-Behalf-Of) authentication token** to the Flowise backend at `openagentic-api:8000` failed with:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Unauthorized\",\n  \"message\": \"No authentication token provided\"\n}\n```\n\n**Affected operations:** `list_chatflows`, `list_nodes`, `create_chatflow`, `create_from_template`, `create_chatflow_advanced`\n\n### Contradiction: Health Check vs Framework Status\n\n| Source | Flowise Status | Endpoint |\n|--------|:--------------:|----------|\n| `flowise_health_check` | ✅ Healthy | Local ping |\n| `get_framework_status` | ❌ Unhealthy | `http://openagentic-api:8000/api/flowise-workspace` |\n\nThe health check is **misleading** — it reports healthy based on a local/shallow check, while the actual API workspace endpoint is unreachable or rejecting tokens.\n\n---\n\n## Correlation with Previous Audits\n\nThis is a **known persistent failure** from previous infrastructure audits:\n\n| Audit | Flowise Status | Notes |\n|-------|:--------------:|-------|\n| **Audit 1** | ❌ Unhealthy | Flowise workspace endpoint unreachable |\n| **Audit 2** | ❌ Unhealthy | Same — persistent across audits |\n| **Audit 3** | ❌ Unhealthy | Same — worsening Loki also observed |\n| **This Test** | ❌ 401 Unauthorized | OBO token not forwarded to Flowise API |\n\n> [!WARNING]\n> **This is the 4th consecutive test confirming Flowise API is non-functional.** The workspace endpoint has been broken across all observed audits. No chatflows can be created, listed, updated, or deleted.\n\n---\n\n## Detailed Template & Guide Data Captured\n\nDespite the API failures, the local MCP functions returned useful configuration data:\n\n### Available Templates\n\n| Template ID | Name | Description |\n|-------------|------|-------------|\n| `simple_conversation` | Simple Conversation | Basic chat with LLM |\n| `conversation_with_memory` | Conversation with Memory | Chat with history retention |\n| `tool_agent` | Tool Agent | Agent with tool calling |\n| `rag_conversation` | RAG Conversation | Document QA with memory |\n| `llm_chain` | LLM Chain | Simple LLM with prompt |\n\n### Recommended Chat Model\n\n- **Node:** `chatOpenAgentic` — unified gateway to Gemini, Claude, GPT, Ollama\n- **Default Model:** `gemini-2.0-flash-001`\n- **Features:** Multi-provider routing, automatic failover, vision support, streaming\n\n---\n\n## Recommendations\n\n| Priority | Action | Rationale |\n|:--------:|--------|-----------|\n| **P0** | **Fix OBO token forwarding** in the MCP proxy → Flowise API path. The token is present (auth_status shows `userAccessToken` exists) but is not being attached to outbound Flowise requests. | **All CRUD operations are blocked.** Zero chatflows can be managed. |\n| **P0** | **Fix the `flowise-workspace` endpoint** at `openagentic-api:8000`. The `get_framework_status` probe confirms it's unhealthy. | Endpoint may be down independently of the auth issue. |\n| **P1** | **Fix `flowise_health_check` to probe the real API**, not just return a local status. It currently gives a false-positive \"healthy\" while the actual backend is down. | Misleading health signal undermines trust in monitoring. |\n| **P1** | **Fix `flowise_get_auth_status` Pydantic validation error** — the `meta` parameter injection is causing a `unexpected_keyword_argument` crash. | Auth debugging tool is itself broken. |\n| **P2** | **Add circuit-breaker logic** — after N consecutive 401s, fail-fast with a clear diagnostic message instead of silently returning 401 on every call. | Improves operator experience during outages. |\n\n---\n\n## Final Scorecard\n\n```\nSteps Completed:     10 attempted\nSteps Passed:         2  (health check, creation guide)\nSteps Failed:         5  (all Flowise API operations)\nSteps Skipped:        5  (cascading from create failure)\nPass Rate:           20%\nLifecycle Complete:   NO — blocked at Step 5 (Create)\nRoot Cause:          OBO token not forwarded + Flowise workspace endpoint unhealthy\nRecurrence:          4th consecutive observation\n```"}

